&quot;IDIOT!!&quot;, shouts Karl Grossemane.<br>
So, while continuing to shout insults at each other, they begin their descent into the airport. They look out of the window and see the shortest runway they have ever seen. Co-pilot Karl Grossemane once again asserts, <br>
&quot;We have got to use a nuke, captain moron, Sir, there is no other freaking alternative, its the only reasonable way for us to be successful.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen you total imbecile, if you disagree with me just one more time I will personally abuse you on the internet for the next one million years. I am the supreme intelligence here and if you dont like it you can take a freaking jump without a freaking parachute.&quot; Yells Captain Bruce Ganglion.<br>
&quot;Hah, I don't care 'cos I have this handy pocket-sized nuclear weapon with which to cushion my fall.&quot; replies Co-pilot Karl Grossemane.<br>
Despite the arguments, they get lined up on final approach with only 50 feet left to go. Things are getting tense as the captain gets the wheels to touch down just inches after the start of the runway.<br>
Immediately, Captain Bruce Ganglion stamps on the brakes, Co-pilot Karl Grossemane slams the engines into full reverse thrust and the plane shudders and howls as the speed comes down. The end of the runway gets closer, beads of sweat appearing on the brows of both our heroes which combine into streams that run down and soak their collars. The passengers are screaming as luggage breaks free of the overhead lockers. People are saying their final prayers as they expect to die. Oh, the humanity!!<br>
But, just as disaster seems inevitable, the plane grinds to a halt with millimeters to spare.<br>
<br>
The noise subsides, the dust settles, and with a quivering voice, Captain Bruce Ganglion looks over to the Co-pilot and says, <br>
&quot;Freaking @#%$!! that has got to be the shortest runway in the world.&quot;<br>
<br>
And, glancing from left to right, Co-pilot Karl Grossemane replies, <br>
&quot;Yeah!!, but look how freaking wide it is!!&quot; <br>
<br>
